    h1 Timestamp Microservice <br><br>

    h2 User Stories
    | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1. The API endpoint is 
    code GET [project_url]/api/timestamp/:date_string?
    p 2. A date string is valid if can be successfully parsed by new Date(date_string). 
    p 3. If the date string is empty it should be equivalent to trigger new Date()
    | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 4. If the date string is valid the api returns a JSON having the structure <br>
    code &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;{"unix": &lt;date.getTime()&gt;, "utc" : &lt;date.toUTCString()&gt; } <br><br>
    | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5. If the date string is invalid the api returns a JSON having the structure <br>
    code &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;{"unix": null, "utc" : "Invalid Date" } <br><br>

    h2 Example Usage
    a(href='/api/timestamp/2015-12-25', target='_blank') [project_url]/api/timestamp/2015-12-25<br>
    a(href='/api/timestamp/1451001600000', target='_blank') [project_url]/api/timestamp/1451001600000 <br><br>

    h2 Example Output
    code &nbsp;&nbsp;{ "unix": 1451001600000, "utc": "Fri, 25 Dec 2015 00:00:00 GMT" }
